ttp://pub83.ezboard.com/uthesensei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Sensei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The MAN.  Damn the MAN.</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#660000>(12/10/01 10:35:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh god no, another fansite pissing match</span><hr size=1> I'm going to do this just because, well, I'm bored, honestly, and I'm so burnt out on this issue it's laughable.  This will be long, so if you're not interested, go clean out the belly button lint or something.  But for you prurient types who care, here's the whole deal.<br><br>First, some history.  Sherman, set the Wayback Machine to July/August.  TPB opens, the successor to my EQ site (The Dojo), one of the widest read EQ pages at the time (even though it was just a *small* profession-specific site, right?).  We have high hopes, E and I, seeing as how AO is a pretty cool game ...<br><br>... with a management company who had no concept of the damage you could do launching something unplayable, unfortunately.  So we sit and watch as fansite after fansite, profession site after profession site and news-site after, you guessed it, news-site, closes its doors.  But we remain hopeful, just like those of you still reading here, that Funcom will come around and wake the hell up, and we try to keep it positive, patch after patch after patch.<br><br>One of the things we do as a site, mostly because I (Sensei) am a former journalist (a real one, believe-it-or-not, with a degree and everything -- not that I consider TPB in any way, shape, or form to be journalism, mind you, but I mention it here because hey, I actually do know a thang or two about the business), and see a value in doing them, is interviews.  God knows no-one addresses real questions from the company on the public forums, and it allows us to get answers for the profession's community that are needed.  So we do one.  Then we try to do a second one, and get blown off for 2 months.<br><br>Somewhere during this time I asked April Jones, the 'Com's US PR tool, to get us on the list for press releases, etc.  It's sort of a logical thing, being a news-site that covers ONE SUBJECT.  Makes sense, right?<br><br>Anyways, back to Rintrah blowing the MA community off for 2 months.  Maybe Funcom was busy, you say.  And you'd be right.  Doing 2 live dev chats and an interview with, you guessed it, AO Basher.  *gasp*  Also during this time, I noticed a press release on, you guessed it, AO Basher , (*gasp*) that we, oddly, didn't get.  <br><br>So I email again.  This time a bit angrier.  Here's the email, and the response (my letter was sent 9/26):<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   OK.  I've been pretty patient about ya'll not replying to the questions in an interview I sent in August 31.  I still say nice things about Funcom on my site, one of the few sites left who does so.  I asked something like 10 questions of you guys.  Simple questions.  Not even very probing questions.  Just things that our class, as players, really wanted to know.  I didn't think this was brain surgery, or that big a pain in the ass.  Apparently I was wrong.<br><br>In the time since I have sent those questions in, you have done 2 2-hour chats with AO Basher and now I log in this morning to find out they are doing a closed interview with Funcom employees tonight.  Um, what in the fuck?  The questions I asked are barely relevent at this point, and it<br>takes a month to get 10 of them answered while you just cater to a single fansite with 3 frigging live interviews?  That's a bad joke.<br><br>I had high hopes for ya'll, but I'm having real second thoughts about how Funcom deals with the fansites and the promises that were made.  So here's one question for you -- should I even bother sending interview reqs in anymore?  It's pretty obvious that you cater just about exclusively to AO Basher, a site hosted on your own servers no less, so should I just not waste my time?  Because this is beyond the limits of professionalism and credulity at this point.  Just let me know because my time is worth more to me than to waste it by sending thoughtful questions your paying customers want to know, and giving you free PR to boot, just to be blown off.<br><br>For a little background, I am former professional journalist who worked in the Colorado daily / weekly news for almost 10 years.  I have interviewed everyone from United States Senators to little girls in beauty pageants and their overbearing mothers.  And I have never, in my entire career, been treated as ridiculously as I am being treated by, of all the frigging things, a video game company -- much less one I am actually helping support.  Maybe ya'll should think about that.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>And the response, sent the same day:<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Hi,<br><br>I am very sorry to hear about your frustration and will do everything possible to address that tomorrow when I have everybody in the office. This includes the amount of time we use on AO-Basher. Other fan-sites have similar concerns. Our goal is to help fans in a way that ensures that there is a wide selection of fan-sites that caters to different interests. It is obvious that we will have to react quicker to requests from more fan-sites to accomplish this.<br><br>The Punching Bag is an important site in the AO community. We really enjoyed the last interview. I hope that we will be able to find a way to reply your requests, now and in the future, in a better way.<br><br>In the short term I will ensure that the interview is finished as soon as possible. Without talking with the people that is working on it, it is difficult to give a specific date. I believe the end of this week is the last estimate you received from us.<br><br>In the long term the Community will work to give The Punching Bag and other fan-sites quicker responses and a better idea about what to expect from us.<br><br>Tor André Wigmostad<br>Funcom Community Manager</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Shortly after this, April gets back to us and gets us on the PR list.<br><br>In the meantime, I keep noticing crap like this, even while TPB, ridiculously enough, is chosen as the AO Site of the Month or something.  I hear about Funcom employees hanging out in Basher's IRC chatroom on patch days.  I see the CR guys posting replies to their news.  I see little insider things like the 2 screenshot thing the other day *seemed* to be (more on that in a bit).  And while all of this is going on I see our profession's concerns getting totally ignored.  We get blown off on bugs that have been fucking up our profession (MA's, for those of you playing the home version of the TPB game and wearing a helmet for your own safety).  We get fed line after line, ETA after missed ETA.<br><br>Then one day I'm reading one of those interviews mentioned in that email to Rintrah (Tor) that Basher did, the closed one I had read about.  And in it I see at least 2-3 times the Basher people stating how they are journalists, etc., and I start laughing, because I've always found that funny (explained below), and maybe a week later I mention it in the news.  Incoming Chaos (from Basher, Senior Editor at the time) email, 11/2:<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Hi Sensei,<br><br>i read your page and had the impression that your in some way &quot;hostile&quot; towards us.  I would kindly ask if we have made anything to make you angry on our site and would like to clear it up because in the actual time the &quot;diversity&quot; in the AO fansites community is very &quot;tight&quot; and we would like to keep a good relationshipt toward other fansites around Anarchy Online.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>To which I responded.  By the way I'm reposting this private correspondence only because I think it's valid, isn't divulging anything private the individuals would not want &quot;out there,&quot; and it saves me from explaining myself 18 times.  Anyways ...<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &gt; Hiyas;<br><br>I don't know that we're any more hostile to you than anyone else we come across on a daily basis, really.  In fact I could point to a few places where I've given you personally, and your site, props for a good question asked, etc.<br><br>However TPB has most definitely taken a few shots at Basher for:<br><br>(1) Being hosted on a Funcom server.  You can argue this until you are blue in the face with us, but it destroys, or at least severely damages, your credibility.  I'd be more than happy to relate to you all of the lectures about conflicts-of-interest that I had in J-School or send you the links, but it shouldn't be neccesary ... I mean ya'll tell us often enough that you're real journalists (tm), so you should know it, right? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Here's the thing ... we're not accusing Basher's editors of being tools of the MAN -- although I have noticed you have bent over for them on at least 1 occassion (the ARK event thing the other day dissapearing, even though it was completely irresponsible to post that in the first place).<br><br>But the question remains: is a conflict of interest, or the risk of one, a big deal in covering video game news?  Yes.  The topic doesn't matter - you either cover something objectively, or you do not, and it doesn't matter if you are running a fansite for a video game or a multinational daily news site.  Now, does Basher seem to be kissing Funcom's ass, as you would expect from this relationship?  Not really.  In fact if you showed me what I consider the three most heavily trafficked AO sites, which are probably Basher, AO Vault and AO Stratics, and asked me which were hosted at Funcom, I'd bet a lot of money that it would have been Stratics and/or Vault.<br><br>Basher, at least recently, hammers Funcom when it's needed, as opposed to the others.  So don't get me wrong here - I'm not accusing Basher of anything more than maintaining a relationship which is a serious broach of ethics in terms of conflict of interest.<br><br>But until you guys are hosted elsewhere, we will most definitely call you out when we think it's appropriate.  If you don't like the stigma, get another host, because you seem intelligent enough to know that issue will not go away.<br><br>(2) We're not big fans of the fact that Funcom has shown you guys preferential treatment in terms of access to Funcom employees to answer questions.  Granted, that's a bit of sour grapes, but it's relatively annoying to us when we have 10 questions emailed to Rintrah (this happened in late-August / early- September) and it takes over a month to get them answered, but in the meantime your site has two or three hour-plus live chats with developers and an interview to boot and E and I are still getting &quot;any day now&quot; from those chuckleheads doing community relations at the 'Com.  <br><br>Not that it's your fault, but you better believe we're going to come out guns blazing on that (aimed at Funcom, which we did), because it's ridiculous -- we've got readers we're responsible to as well.<br><br>(3) I always notice when I see someone say &quot;I'm a real reporter&quot; in news coverage.  As a former reporter and editor I just find it funny (and therefore a valid target for satire).  If you have to tell someone this, especially 3-4 times in the same interview, you're not one, you're just roleplaying one.<br><br>Honestly I think that pretty much summarizes the only things we've ever nailed Basher on in the daily news thang.  Personally I hit Basher daily, use the site's map database exclusively and even hit your forums occasionally.  And E and I have pointed to your site several times for our readers to check something out.  So don't take us laughing at you occasionally the wrong way, Chaos -- we're hostile to pretty much everything at some point or the other.  It has nothing to do with good/bad relationships with yours or any other site nor is it our stance that &quot;j00 suxx0r&quot; or that we pick on Basher -- we simply call things the way we see them as they occur.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>So that's about where we stood until last week, when I'm running through the usual 10 sites I check to see if I've missed something newsworthy and the Offical Forums for news for you bums.  I hit Basher and lo and behold, they have 2 screenshots of a new dungeon which I had assumed was the one mentioned in the 13.4 patch notes I had just finished copying in.  I read the comments and there's Cz saying something about them.  So I check Vault.  Nothing.  Stratics.  Nothing.  Lore?  Zilch.  TPB's Inbox?  Bzzzztt.<br><br>Now if that doesn't look like an exclusive, I don't know what does.  Apparently the other sites did get that mail, we're just the whipping boy or something.  And I'm seeing fucking red, man, bigtime.  Same shit, different month.  Then I notice that one of TPB's own forum-dwellers, Dragonfly, has gotten roasted on Basher too, which pisses me off to no end.  If you don't get that, how would you like it if you opened your daily newspaper one day and Joe Blow down the street was being lambasted on the front page in some kindergarden-esque rant for no other reason than there was no better news?  Dragonfly may be a class A asshole, but who cares?  He didn't deserve to be singled out like that, period.  It's unprofessional at best and downright inexcusible at worst.  <br><br>And no, Dragonfly having a website doesn't excuse it.  You don't do things like this if you purport to be a &quot;professional news site&quot; run by &quot;professional journalists.&quot;  That is, unless, you do it to people regularly.  But Basher didn't -- Dragon was singled out of the crowd and hammered, and as far as I'm concerned that's disgusting.  And just stupid, given the fodder of AO Basher's legions of regularly posting dipshits like CaptFallout who just beg for the treatment.<br><br>But I'm digressing.  Anywho, I go off in the news, because, hey, I go off in the news every day.  Friday it was Funcom's turn.  Not Basher's, if you read the news.  I even checked myself on how annoyed I was at that Dragonfly thing.  But you better believe I t'd off 100% on Funcom, whom I think deserves it.  But Sion got a bug in his ass that someone was attacking Basher, and so I get ridiculed by a small host of uneducated kiss-asses.  Sniffle.<br><br>So let's get started, shall we?  First, Sion, thank you for whatever you did to get us on the PREMIERE VIDEO GAME NEWS DISTRIBUTION LIST.  Nice to know Funcom listens to at least one website, because they sure as hell don't listen to ours.  Secondly, Cz, since I replied to your private email about this (which I won't reprint here, since it's repetitive and doesn't shed any new light here except you wanting to know why you were the victim Friday) with this url, feel free to jump on in here, because I'm really dying to know, as I'm sure the 2 other people actively interested in this thead are, why it takes 5 frigging months to get something accomplished like being on a distribution list.<br><br>Third, if I offended anyone at Basher, Funcom, this community, AO players in general, the almighty CaptFallout or the company that makes those tongue-like vibrators, GOOD.  Be offended.  Buy tissue, it will happen again.  That's what I sell here.  If you don't like it, feel free to hit that door over there like a bat out of Hell.  I don't sell news here and not only do I not promise to be unbiased, I promise to be so biased that if you don't read at least one of the daily updates and go &quot;what a