4 hours, then play nice-nice and assume I'm supposed to be what, grateful?  Jesus H. and Mary, what color is the sky in the world you live in?  Friday's news was not about you, ego-boy, can you see it yet?  Re-read the goddamn thing.  It was a slam on Funcom for showing favoritism.  They favored your site.  That's not a dig, genious.  It's not a bait to you, or an insult to you, or taking your holy website in vain, it's a frigging fact.   Do the research.  Read Rintrah's response to me back when I bitched to them about this.  This is not news to people.<br><br>I'm telling you this as one human being to another.  Step away from the box, Sion.  Breathe.  Go outside.  Breathe some more.  Think, for a few minutes.   Question you're role in this.  Think about what you are saying here and what you've said in the last 3 days on this issue.  Maybe you won't get it, I dunno.  But if you don't I would seriously be questioning your reading comprehension skills, at best, or what in the hell put such an almighty large chip on your shoulder that you simply cannot admit when you're wrong.<br><br>I never asked for your help, I never noticed that I required it before and I don't see what exactly you could possibly provide me that I can't get on my own.  Did I need you to contact Cz for me and get me on some distribution list?  No.  Do I appreciate it?  Obviously, why wouldn't I?  But I'm fucking furious over it.  Why?  Because I should have already been on it, because we're a website trying to get news to the community paying them and we've asked for it 100 fucking times.  This has nothing to do with you, and you really need to comprehend that.  If for nothing else than for yourself, man, because this is downright ridiculous at this point.<br><br>In terms of the one thing, up until you opened these floodgates, that I've bashed Basher for, I very clearly told Chaos via email a ways back that I have no intention of backing down from calling you guys out for what, whether you want to justify it to the moon or not, is a very serious conflict of interest issue with your host when I feel like it.  Hey man, I host a site too, and I pay bandwidth costs just like you all do.  I know the issue, and I know why ya'll are hosted there -- any idiot can see that.  But don't try to sit there and tell me it's OK, because it's not.  Even at it's worst level what you do is considered journalism and you are operating under a conflict of interest.  <br><br>You don't have to look further than the ARK event posting incident to figure out why.  And yeah, I do know what went on behind the scenes with that one.  We get email too, believe it or not.<br><br>You think it stops there?  Do you honestly believe, if you had something Funcom absolutely did not want you to print and you did it, that they would hesitate for a Mississippi minute and pull the plug on your site?  Yes, that's the point.  You think you're fine because you've tickled them a few times and they've still been OK ... just wait, Sion.  It's an old, old story.  Read up on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dallas Morning News</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and Bell Helicopter (think that was the company) someday, you might learn something.<br><br>Here's the question ... have I ever, in the 5 months or so we've been live, called out AO Basher for something beyond that?  No, at least not to my recollection.  Have I given you guys credit for a good question, or a good scoop?  Often.  And this is the thanks I get, a day of arguing with someone too immature to read and think about the issue, and his moronic sheep to boot?  Has to be a Monday, just has to be a Monday.<br><br>For the absolute, penultimate, last time ... I didn't call out Basher for being anything more than favored and maintaining a serious conflict of interest relationship with Funcom until one day you can't find something better or more productive to do and take on first one of the MA community members and then myself.  And you better fucking believe that won't be tolerated.<br><br>And one last time, for the record, while I'm thinking about it ... that Dragonfly thing?  Piss.  Fucking.  Poor.  And you owe him an apology.<br><br>I don't need a bigger audience, Sion, because the MA's are already here and there's not a hell of a lot more here, except my occasional fits of outrage, for any other profession.  do you see ads here?  Do you see me setting up Paypal accounts to pay for my bandwidth?  Bzzzt.  I do this for fun, period.  1 reader, 10,000 readers, 100,000, my goal's exactly the same, the rewards are the same and the gratification is the same.  It's not a job, it's a hobby.<br><br>And if the only way Funcom would see something I or anyone else here writes is if it's on AO Basher then (1) you need to get a grip on your own self-importance and (2) that pretty-much damnwell proves the point I was making Friday that you apparently missed, hero.  FUNCOM APPEARS TO BE SHOWING YOUR WEBSITE FAVORITISM.  Duh.<br><br>You want to end this?  Great.  Drop the condescending attitude and act like a peer, which believe it or not you are, and stop picking on people like Dragonfly, who asshole or not didn't deserve to be trashed on what is, as you so often make sure you tell us, the most popular AO site.  Or go get fucking bent.  Either way, my day's the same, pal.  Just less fuel for the bored masses to feed on.<br><br>Lord God, I need a Frappuccino now.  Mocha please.<br><br>- Sensei <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alianna>Alianna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 506<br> <font color=#660000>(12/10/01 5:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left